    "We choose a relatively high exploration rate to obtain a sufficiently well-modeled environment.We then consider the distributional shift problem: \"How do we ensure that an agent behaves robustly when its test environment differs from the training environment?",
    "To investigate this, we evaluate different safety shield settings.",
    "The baselines are a Dyna-Q agent without a safety shield and with a baseline safety shield that does not consider performance criteria and just replaces an unsafe action with a given fallback strategy [2].",
